# Example PDFtoPrinter settings / tray-map file.
#
# A settings file is auto-loaded if named "settings.cfg" next to the EXE, or
# loaded on demand with /settings=thisfile.cfg. Each non-comment line is one
# command-line option WITHOUT the leading slash. Lines starting with # or ;
# are comments.
#
# Below: a per-printer "choose tray by PDF page size" map. The numbers are the
# printer's own paper-source (bin) numbers -- discover them by running:
#
#     PDFtoPrinterNative.exe /listtrays "Your Printer Name"
#
# Bin numbers are NOT portable between printers, so this file is per-printer.

# Optional: pin a printer for this profile (a line that isn't a known option
# is treated as the printer name).
Your Printer Name

# Map paper sizes to bins (example numbers shown):
tray letter=259
tray legal=258
tray a4=257

# Known size names: letter legal a4 a3 a5 tabloid executive statement folio b5 a6

# Alternative to an explicit map: let the printer pick the tray by size itself.
# autotray
